Review control description: (3) The provisions contained in paragraphs 6 to19, 23 to 33 and 50 to 52 shall
be applicable to NBFCs of the above-mentioned categories in sub-para (2)
for all layers;

Review control description: (4) The provisions contained in paragraphs 53 to 57 shall be applicable to
NBFCs of the above-mentioned categories in sub-para (2) for Middle Layer
and above;

Review control description: (6) The provisions contained in Paragraph 6, Paragraphs 7 to 14 and 40 to 49
shall be applicable to Housing Finance Company (HFC) registered with the
RBI;

Review control description: (7) The provisions contained in Paragraphs 26 to 33 and 50 to 51 shall be
applicable to NBFC- Standalone Primary Dealer (NBFC-SPD) registered
with the RBI;

Review control description: In this context, 'RE' shall mean:
(1) Commercial Banks (including Small Finance Banks, Local Area Banks and
Regional Rural Banks);

Review control description: The overseas investment in a single entity,
including its stepdown subsidiaries, by way of equity or fund-based
commitment shall not be more than 15 percent of the NBFC's owned funds;

Review control description: (5) Overseas investment shall not involve multi-layered, cross jurisdictional
structures and at most only a single intermediate holding entity shall be
permitted;

Review control description: (13) SPVs set up abroad or acquisition abroad shall be treated as investment or
subsidiary / joint venture abroad, depending upon percentage of investment
in overseas entity;

Review control description: In addition, the following conditions shall apply:
(1) The parent NBFC shall not extend implicit or explicit guarantee to or on
behalf of such subsidiaries;

Review control description: However, companies
undertaking activities such as financial consultancy and advisory services
with no significant assets shall not be considered as shell companies;

Review control description: <image>
(5) The overseas subsidiary shall not be used as a vehicle for raising resources
for creating assets in India for the Indian operations;

Review control description: (6) The parent NBFC shall obtain periodical reports / audit reports about the
business undertaken by the subsidiary abroad and shall make them available
to the RBI and inspecting officials of the RBI;

Review control description: (7) If the overseas subsidiary fails to undertake any activity or if the required
reports are not submitted, the RBI may review or withdraw the approval given
for setting up a subsidiary abroad;

Review control description: (b) The WOS/JV being established abroad by the CIC shall not be used
as a vehicle for raising resources for creating assets in India for the
Indian operations;

Review control description: (d) If the WOS/JV has not undertaken any activity or such reports are
not forthcoming, the approvals given for setting up the WOS/JV
abroad shall be reviewed;

Review control description: There should be no 'linkage' either direct or indirect
between the provision of financial services offered by the HFC to its
customers and use of the insurance products;

Review control description: (iii) The level of net non-performing assets should be not more than 3% of
the total outstanding assets, including loans and advances taken
together;

Review control description: (v) An NBFC shall neither acquire units of mutual funds from the secondary
market for sale to its customers, nor shall it buy back units of mutual
funds from its customers;

Review control description: The code of conduct
prescribed by SEBI, as amended from time to time and as applicable,
shall be complied with by the NBFC undertaking this activity;

Review control description: An Infrastructure Debt Fund (IDF) shall be established either as:
(1) a trust, registered as an IDF-Mutual Fund and regulated by the Securities
and Exchange Board of India (SEBI);

Review control description: Further, the repeal of these directions, instructions,
or guidelines shall not in any way prejudicially affect:
